bug.author: TylerADavis
bug.summary: Broken links on "Importing a TensorFlow GraphDef based Models into TensorFlow.js"
bug.description:
<denchmark-h:h2>URL(s) with the issue:</denchmark-h>
<denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/js/tutorials/conversion/import_saved_model>https://www.tensorflow.org/js/tutorials/conversion/import_saved_model</denchmark-link>
<denchmark-h:h2>Description of issue (what needs changing):</denchmark-h>
This page contains a link that seems to suggest it has either a description of a Frozen Model (the clickable text is Frozen Model) or a description of how to use one. However, the link appears dead, and simply redirects to the main TF Lite webpage. Link: <denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/mobile/prepare_models#how_do_you_get_a_model_you_can_use_on_mobile>https://www.tensorflow.org/mobile/prepare_models#how_do_you_get_a_model_you_can_use_on_mobile</denchmark-link>
There is also a dead link (404) to Session Bundles: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/session_bundle/README.md>https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/session_bundle/README.md</denchmark-link>
<denchmark-h:h3>Correct links</denchmark-h>
I am not sure of the correct links that should be substituted in here, or if these links should perhaps be removed entirely.

comments.comment: Submitted a fix to remove links ,as both saved model and session bundle are deprecated.Thanks for reporting.
